The paper presents a framework for creating reproducible robotic environments for reinforcement learning research, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of OpenAI Gym interface, which is a popular framework for reinforcement learning, and the distributed simulation capability, which relates to systems and control (cs.SY). The paper mentions the use of rendering engines, which could relate to computer vision (cs.CV), and the software architecture provides abstraction of the Robot and the Task, which could relate to machine learning (cs.LG).
